The national government will soon implement an accord with Tanzania on Mara River conservation.Water CS Eugene Wamalwa said the framework on urban waste management, water management and pollution is being developed. The framework will also study effects on conservation of people living along the basin.Wamalwa said sustainable management of the shared water resource will improve conservation. He spoke in Bomet on Thursday during the 5th Mara Day celebrations. The CS called for continued support between the two countries. Council of Governors chairman Peter Munya said the new laws give too much power to water management authorities. He said counties will manage the agencies better.Bomet Governor Isaac Rutto said his government has planted trees along rivers and banned car washing along the rivers as conservation measures.